  "body": "My App is currently stacked in a Provider-->followed by Parent AppContainer Component-->followed by actual component.\r\nM using Snapshot testing to load a component and call methods on it.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n const tree = renderer\r\n      .create(\r\n        <Provider store={store}>\r\n          <AppContainer>\r\n              <MyComponent />\r\n          </AppContainer>\r\n        </Provider>\r\n)\r\nvar instance = tree.getInstance()\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis gives me instance of the Provider component. How do i get instance of MyComponent, to be able to call its methods?\r\n\r\n\r\nI tried to do\r\n```js\r\nconst tree = renderer\r\n      .create(\r\n              <MyComponent store={store} />\r\n\r\n)\r\n```\r\n, but this gives error, as it not able to resolve 'CONTEXT', and i see that there is no way to pass context.\r\n\r\nAny help?\r\n\r\n\r\n",
